From 18752666b9bf902a72515b92c516ae5210bd78b1 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: wedge100s-port <wedge100s@local>
Date: 2026-03-17
Subject: [PATCH] fix: vxlanorch.h expose doTask via using declaration

VxlanTunnel inherits from both Orch and OrchDaemon.  Orch defines
multiple doTask() overloads; without a using declaration the private
virtual doTask(swss::SelectableTimer&) hides Orch::doTask(Consumer&),
causing a compilation ambiguity with newer compilers (GCC 12+).

Add `using Orch::doTask;` in the private section to make all Orch
overloads visible alongside the specialised timer variant.
---
 orchagent/vxlanorch.h | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/orchagent/vxlanorch.h b/orchagent/vxlanorch.h
index ae7cd85..8bd0d24 100644
--- a/orchagent/vxlanorch.h
+++ b/orchagent/vxlanorch.h
@@ -372,6 +372,7 @@ public:


 private:
+    using Orch::doTask;
     virtual bool addOperation(const Request& request);
     virtual bool delOperation(const Request& request);
     void doTask(swss::SelectableTimer&);
